      section(data-bespoke-hash='start-of-time')
        h1 1969
        p.bullet The history of UNIX starts in this year with Ken Thompson, Dennis Ritchie and others started working on the "little used PDP-7 in a corner" at Bell Labs
        h2.bullet 1 January 1970
        p.bullet The start of time 
        h2.bullet 1971 First Edition UNIX
        h2.bullet 1973 Fourth Edition
        p.bullet Rewritten in C -this made it portable and changed the history of <dfn title="Operating System">OS</dfn>s

      section(data-bespoke-hash='bsd')
        h2 1975
        p.bullet UNIX leaves AT&amp;T and <dfn title="Berkley Software Distribution">BSD</dfn> is born at Computer Systems Research Group (CSRG) of the University of California, Berkeley.
        h2.bullet 1980
        p.bullet XENIX Microsoft does UNIX
        p.bullet and 4BSD arrives

